This paper is about natural language processing and machine translation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of data selection and parameter sharing, which are techniques commonly used in optimization and neural network training (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of machine translation systems, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
